value.value: 虹彩角膜角の異常
any structural anomaly of the acute angle occurring between the iris and the cornea at the periphery of the anterior chamber of the eye
癒着

an adhesion (synechia) of the iris to the cornea or lens of the eye that may develop from glaucoma, cataracts, uveitis, or keratitis or as a complication of surgery or trauma to the eye; synechiae may prevent or impede flow of aqueous fluid between the anterior and posterior chambers of the eye, resulting in angle closure glaucoma
小柱網の再生不良
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the trabecular meshwork of the eye, typically resulting in decreased size
小柱網の欠如
absence of the pore-like structure surrounding the entire circumference of the anterior chamber through which aqueous humor circulates
卵円孔開存
incomplete closure of the atrial septum after birth, resulting in a flap or a valve-like opening in the atrial septal wall
シュレム管の欠如
absence of the vascular structure encircling the anterior chamber of the eye, through which the aqueous humor is returned to the blood circulation

胎仔赤血球の新生異常
anomaly in the development of primarily large, nucleated erythroblasts occurring in blood islands in the yolk sac, generally occurs from E7-E11 in the mouse and through 10 weeks in humans
胎仔赤血球の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the embryonic blood cells that carry oxygen; embryonic erythrocytes arise from yolk sac blood islands and express different types of hemoglobins (beta-H1, gamma-1 and zeta) than adult erythrocytes, and can enucleate in circulation
カルシウムイオン恒常性異常
anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium of calcium ions within the body or between a cell and its external environment
筋肉重量の減少
less than average muscle weight
筋肉重量の異常
any anomaly in the average muscle weight
咀嚼筋の形態異常
any structural anomaly of any of the muscles responsible for the movement of the jaws during mastication, including the masseter, temporal, and medial and lateral pterygoid muscles
咬筋の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the masticatory muscle of posterior cheek with origin from the inferior border and medial surface of the zygomatic arch, with insertion into the lateral surface of the ramus of the mandible, with nerve supply from the masseteric nerve, and whose action closes the jaw during chewing
咬筋の欠如
absence of the masticatory muscle of posterior cheek
翼状筋の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the muscles descending from the sphenoid bone to the lower jaw including the internal, or medial, pterygoid muscle and external, or lateral, pterygoid muscle; the action of the former is closing the jaws and that of the latter is opening the jaws, protruding the mandible, and moving the mandible from side to side
翼状筋の欠如
absence of either the internal or external or of both pterygoid muscles
側頭筋の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the superior-most masticatory muscle whose action is closing the jaws; its posterior portion retracts the mandible
側頭筋の形態欠如
absence of the superior-most masticatory muscle whose action is closing the jaws; its posterior portion retracts the mandible
棘融解
separation of prickle cells of the spinous layer of the epidermis, resulting in atrophy of the prickle cell layer, as in conditions such as pemphigus vulgaris and Darier disease
形質細胞様樹状細胞の形態異常

any structural anomaly of phagocytic dendritic cells that are morphologically similar to plasma cells, but do not express B lineage markers, and produce large amounts of alpha/beta interferons (IFN-/) in response to viral and bacterial stimuli; plasmacytoid dendritic cells are found in the thymic medulla and lymph node T cell areas and are responsible for immune tolerance
運動神経の発達異常

aberrant response of a motor neuron to form new neuritic processes (sprouts) that emerge from the nodes of Ranvier or terminal arborizations in response to nerve injury (such as denervation), application of nerve toxin, or muscle inactivity (usually due to disease)
流産率の異常
change in frequency of a natural or accidental termination of a pregnancy at a stage where the embryo or the fetus is incapable of surviving independently of the mother
生殖器の出血
bleeding into the genitals
(肢の)長指伸筋の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the penniform muscle of the lateral front part of the leg responsible for extension of the toes and dorsiflexion of the ankle
膵臓の矮小化
decrease of the size of the pancreas compared to controls
(筋板由来の)筋の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the muscles derived from the medial myotome; includes the intrinsic back muscles
膨大部稜の形態異常

any structural anomaly in the elevation found on the inner surface of the ampullae of each semicircular duct; filaments of the vestibular nerve pass through the crista to reach hair cells on its surface; the hair cells are capped by the cupula, a gelatinous protein-polysaccharide mass
タウタンパク質の沈着

formation of self-assembled tangles of paired helical filaments and straight filaments due to hyperphosphorylation of the tau protein; often seen in neuronal tissues of individuals with neurodegenerative disorders
(心臓発生における)ループ化の失敗
failure of the primitive heart tube to loop asymmetrically during early development
ループ形態形成の方向異常
deviation from the characteristic rightward direction of looping of the primitive heart tube; frequently seen in heterotaxy syndromes
心耳の二分化
a cardiac anomaly whereby the left or right atrial appendage is cleaved, forming two separate pouches connected by a thin strand of muscular tissue
脳のアミロイド血管障害

a pathological condition where there is a deposition of amyloid in the walls of the small cerebral vessels which supply the brain; this results in an increased risk of infarcts and/or intracerebral hemorrhage, possibly resulting in dementia
海綿状栄養膜層の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the middle layer of the placenta between the outermost giant cells and the innermost labyrinth layer; it has a structural role and also produces several layer-specific secreted factors
母系脱落膜層の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the maternal uterine-derived portion of the placenta
胎盤重量の異常
any change in the weight of the organ of metabolic interchange between fetus and mother
胎盤サイズの異常
anomaly in the size or shape of the organ of metabolic interchange between fetus and mother
胎盤の矮小化
reduced size of the size or shape of the organ of metabolic interchange between fetus and mother
胎盤の肥大化
increased size of the size or shape of the organ of metabolic interchange between fetus and mother
胎仔神経上皮の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the epithelial cell layer that lines the neural tube and develops into the nervous system and into the neural crest cells
身体物理的強度の異常
altered ability of an organism to exert force on physical objects or of the body to support its load
四肢異型
atypical intentionally or habitually assumed position of the limbs compared to the normal carriage of the body

definition.value: This term should not be used to describe abnormal limb placement on the body (congenital or trauma induced).

value.value: 胚外組織の生理異常
any functional anomaly of the membranes involved with embryonic protection and nutrition
胎盤輸送の異常
anomaly in the conveyance of metabolic products and nutrients across the placenta
蒼白色の胎盤
placenta lacking normal reddish coloration, often refers to bloodless condition
視索の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the paired bands of optic nerve fibers running from the optic chiasma mostly to the lateral geniculate body, with a smaller number of fibers terminating in the superior colliculus and the pretectal region
眼柄の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the narrow, proximal portion of the optic vesicle which connects the embryonic eye and forebrain
眼杯の形態異常

any structural anomaly of double walled structure formed by expansion and invagination of the distal end of the optic vesicle that develops into the pigmented and neuronal layers of the retina, with the mouth of the optic cup developing into the pupil of the eye
鎮痛
inability to sense pain
